The TRT utilizes high pressured gas emitted from the steel blast furnace and converts the pressured energy into mechanical energy to drive the turbine units and generate electricity. The CHPG collects and utilizes medium to low temperature wasted steam and gas emitted from production process of the cement rotary kilns to generate electricity.
